    "6. Key Insights Summary\n",
    "# \tFinding \t                                                                    Statistical Evidence\n",
    "1 \tSex is the strongest survival predictor \t                            χ²=260.7, p<0.001, Cramér's V=0.54 (large)\n",
    "2 \tFare correlates with survival (r=0.33) but doesn't cause it \t        Class-based lifeboat access is the mechanism\n",
    "3 \tAge alone does not predict survival \t                                Welch t-test p=0.058; Mann-Whitney p=0.270\n",
    "4 \tPclass drives both Fare and survival probability \t                    Mediator variable; classic confounding\n",
    "5 \tFare is highly right-skewed (skew≈4.8); log-transform normalises it \tEssential preprocessing step\n",
    "\n",
    "    Correlation ≠ Causation: First-class passengers paid more and survived more — but wealth didn't save them directly. It determined their cabin deck, which determined proximity to lifeboats.\n"
   ]
